point  the original cleric was in a using mode.  the SK wasnt a person to the cleric.  The SK was a toon to be used for the clerics goal of camping a BP.<br>
<br>
<br>
people in a using mode can...  STFU! <br>
<br>
people get narrow eyes when they get around loot  *they want*.  The very idea that you would offer someone &quot;exp&quot; if you can have the &quot;exp + loot&quot;  is gross.  you came for the exp so you should service me type peeps prolly wouldnt do that if they got their eyes outside the situation. Maytbe they could have killed the named without the sk but they needed the sk to make the camp more tenuable themselves so the SK did fill a role.  Maybe they could have found a tank more amiable to being used.  Maybe but doesnt make users right if the people they are using are ok with it?  to each their own i guess but i certainly dont think it makes it ok.  then the game becomes this fight amoung dominate egos and mass acquiescing <br>
<br>
To me this would be similiar to joining a group with a druid who wanted to go solo names on track when they popped up (if it were possible).  Dont worry though group the druid would *solo* the named and would be available for the groups exp role for the druid 99% of the time.   The difference here is the &quot;druid&quot; is 4 people.  but the &quot;druid&quot; is still behaving the same way.  Why would it be wrong for a lone individual to behave that way and right for 4 people to do the same thing? At some point you have to go well damn right wrong or side ways thats just self serving objectifying your other players like that.<br>
<br>
thats what happened here.  a  cleric objectified another player. the other player ran round angry bout being an object instead of a person.    <br>
